{"id": "1445700494512361554", "channel_id": "1444660129525006427", "author_id": "96239108967395328", "author_name": "soramaru", "content": "It's important to maintain good will with your  customers. Bug or not, there are people who roll for gmurphy because of the sacrifice mechanic and   the current changes to the mechanic (that also come 1 week after) does negatively impact the character. \n\nYou have a lot of newbies joining the game now but most of them are gonna drop the game once the anniversary is over. The number of those that remain will be based on their first impression which is already honestly not great due to the poor oversight on the raid implementation that is not good for newcomers with small character and posse pool.\n\nBut even if the raid event is flawed other aspects of the game don't have to be bad. You can still win smaller battles like this issue here. The sudden surge and popularity of morimens is from word of mouth of your fans. As long as you keep a majority of your fan base happy, your game community will grow when happy fans recommend the game to others. It's free advertising and marketing.\n\nIt's fine to maintain your stance on things regarding game vision like the difficulty, most players can respect and understand that but this issue here is not really about game vision but about being fair. You can nerf, buff or fix mechanic according to your game vision and still compensate those who roll for gmurphy before the fix. \n\nMind you I have oe gmurphy and I intend to keep her reset or no. So I don't have much stakes in this but if this is how nerfs or bug fixes are handled in game, I will naturally be much more cautious in spending.", "timestamp": "2025-12-03T08:57:37.708000+00:00", "thread_id": "1444660129525006427", "edited_timestamp": "2025-12-03T09:02:11.026000+00:00", "reactions": [{"emoji": "✅", "emoji_id": null, "count": 5}, {"emoji": "👍", "emoji_id": null, "count": 2}]}
